videos.description: Miami kicks off their game against Duke with an alley-oop dunk from Sheldon McClellan.
videos.headline: Sheldon McClellan sets the tone with a dunk to start the first half

videos.description: 1H (16:40) DUKE Luke Kennard made Jumper.
videos.headline: Luke Kennard with a sweet three point play

videos.headline: Brandon Ingram dribbles, drives, and dunks

videos.description: 1H (12:26) MIA Kamari Murphy made Dunk. Assisted by Ja'Quan Newton.
videos.headline: Ja'Quan Newton grabs the offensive board and dishes a nice bounce pass to Kamari Murphy for a dunk

videos.description: Duke super frosh Brandon Ingram drives to the hoop but steps on the foot of Miami's James Palmer. Ingram gets called for a travel but stays in the game.
videos.headline: Ingram steps on a foot

videos.description: 1H (10:30) MIA James Palmer made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Davon Reed.
videos.headline: Miami players are on fire behind the arc, James Palmer hits one from deep

videos.headline: Both teams are bringing it all the way down to the end of the first half; both hit from three

videos.description: Jim Larranaga Halftime Interview
videos.headline: Jim Larranaga Halftime Interview

videos.description: Miami's Angel Rodriguez feeds Kamari Murphy down low with a beautiful pass that leads to a two-handed slam against Duke.
videos.headline: This crowd goes crazy for a dime

videos.description: Sheldon McClellan drives from the baseline and catches an alley-oop pass from Ja'Quan Newton, slamming it down for the dunk.
videos.headline: McClellan takes flight

videos.description: In the final seconds of the Hurricanes' 80-69 win over Duke, Ja'Quan Newton gets the ball in transition and punishes the rim with a thunderous dunk.
videos.headline: Miami finishes with a flush

videos.description: Miami coach Jim Larrañaga gives a shout out to his players for shutting down Duke in an 80-69 victory.
videos.headline: Larrañaga praises defensive performance in win over Duke

videos.description: Sean McDonough and Dick Vitale recaps Miami's 80-69 win over Duke, in which Angel Rodriguez controlled the floor with his spacing, shooting and passing.
videos.headline: Rodriguez paces Hurricanes past Blue Devils
